You could use a [`local-exec` provisioner][1] to use the AWS CLI to trigger your Glue crawler once it is created:

```hcl
resource &quot;aws_glue_crawler&quot; &quot;my_crawler&quot; {
  database_name = &quot;my_db&quot;
  name          = &quot;my_crawler&quot;
  role          = &quot;arn:aws:iam::111111111111:role/service-role/someRole&quot;

  s3_target {
    path = &quot;s3://my_bucket/key/prefix&quot;
  }

  provisioner &quot;local-exec&quot; {
    command = &quot;aws glue start-crawler --name ${self.name}&quot;
  }
}
```

This would be only triggered when creating the crawler and not at any other point, such as if you changed the `s3_target.path` or anything else.

If you wanted to be able to trigger this when changing the `s3_target.path` you&#39;d need to use a [`null_resource` with a `trigger`][2]:

```hcl
resource &quot;aws_glue_crawler&quot; &quot;my_crawler&quot; {
  database_name = &quot;my_db&quot;
  name          = &quot;my_crawler&quot;
  role          = &quot;arn:aws:iam::111111111111:role/service-role/someRole&quot;

  s3_target {
    path = &quot;s3://my_bucket/key/prefix&quot;
  }
}

resource &quot;null_resource&quot; &quot;run_crawler&quot; {
  # Changes to the crawler&#39;s S3 path requires re-running
  triggers = {
    s3_path = &quot;${aws_glue_crawler.my_crawler.s3_target.0.path}&quot;
  }

  provisioner &quot;local-exec&quot; {
    command = &quot;aws glue start-crawler --name ${self.name}&quot;
  }
}
```


  [1]: https://www.terraform.io/docs/provisioners/local-exec.html
  [2]: https://www.terraform.io/docs/providers/null/resource.html

